OL,4,Cbombing to take part in inquiry
OL,6,FThose affected by the 1998 Omagh
OL,7,Fbombing are being invited to
OL,8,Fparticipate in a public inquiry into
OL,9,Fthe atrocity.
OL,11,FScottish judge Lord Turnbull, who
OL,12,Fchairs the inquiry, said he needed to
OL,13,Ffully understand the significance of
OL,14,Fthe bombing and its impact.
OL,16,FThe Omagh Bombing Inquiry will host
OL,17,Ffour weeks of commemorative and
OL,18,Fpersonal statement hearings in January
OL,19,Fand February of next year.
